SIMPLE: whipperin
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Whipperin
<hw>Whip"per*in`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>1.</sn> <def>A huntsman who keeps the hounds from wandering, and
whips them in, if necessary, to the of chase.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Hence, one who enforces the discipline of a party,
and urges the attendance and support of the members on all necessary
occasions.</def><-- = whip, 6 (a) -->⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Whippersnapper</ent>⟦br⟧
